<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>[ . . . will pay to] the aerarium <gap extent="unknown" reason="lost" unit="character"/> The memorial of Aelia Ammia and Aelius Pappias the children of Papias. A copy of this was deposited in the property-archive in the third stephanephorate of Ti(berius) Fl(avius) Xaireas, month Xandikos.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The nomenclature fits a date earlier than the Edict of Caracalla. The reference to the aerarium is unusual (<xref type="inscription" n="1549" href="120320">12.320</xref> =MAMA 556b, &amp; LR cj. in <xref type="inscription" n="1534" href="120524">12.524</xref> =MAMA 559</p>
</div>
